what exactly is a nervous breakdown what happends in what most people call a nervous breakdown the person usually loses touch with the reality that we all share they will usually hear things or see things that only they can see and hear of course to them this is real and they don't understand why we don't see and hear the things that they do most mental health professional call this a psycholtic break it can take a while to bring them back to our reality and it usally involves medications and a strict monetreing of their intake of their medications if most people stick with their medications and see their therapist they can usually live pretty normal lives of course there are some exceptions to that rule but for the most part if they stick with their medicines and therapy their be ok for the most part Medicine Psychosis Milton H. Erickson Traumatic brain injury Reparative therapy Autism Massage Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Theory of conduct Physical therapy Mental illness Transactional analysis Psychotherapy Osteopathy Alfred Korzybski Mental Health Act 1983 Involuntary commitment Psychoanalysis Panic attack Cancer Anorexia nervosa Psychiatry Traumatic incident reduction Clinical depression Multiple sclerosis Scenes from a Memory Hypertension Controversies in autism Dissociative identity disorder Scientology beliefs and practices Nurse Traditional Chinese medicine Professional wrestling match types Hypoglycemia Hearing impairment Palliative care Childbirth Glossary of medical terms related to communications disorders Reality Mental health Infantilism Drug abuse Stuttering Transsexuality Urinary incontinence Occupational Therapy Addiction Cyberspace Hypnosis Schizophrenia Medical cannabis Folic acid Ex-gay Bipolar disorder Medical record Cerebral palsy Borderline personality disorder Stem cell Diabetes mellitus House of M Chronic fatigue syndrome Triage Religious Society of Friends Electroconvulsive therapy Abduction Phenomenon Rudolf Hermann Lotze Sports medicine National